   <text>
      <!-- ged: I changed the p element that is within the body element to ab becuase 
      I think this is more of an anonymous block of information from the source rather than a paragraph..
      Also I added a hi element to display any text that was underlined or written in a different color. 
      I added various attributes to other elements as well like the div element. I tried to use figure and 
      graphic elements to describe the images and drawings on the page-->
      <body>
         <div n="1" type="calenderEntry">
            <ab>
               <date>
                  <lb/>January 30, 1909. <lb/>Saturday </date>
               <lb/>
               <figure>
                  <figDesc>A man sitting in bed looking at his alarm clock on the nightstand table.
                     The image is in black and white.</figDesc>
                  <graphic
                     url="https://newtfire.org/courses/tutorials/TEI-images/mary-behrend-calendar-1909/IMG_2041.jpg"
                  />
               </figure>
               <lb/><name>E.R.B</name>
               <quote>
                  <lb/>"That damned old clock <lb/>give me a ????? <lb/>Each morning when it's dark
                     <lb/><hi rend="underline">It likes</hi> the fun, but I'm ????? <lb/>To tire of
                  the dark!" </quote>
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div n="2" type="calenderEntry">
            <ab>
               <date>
                  <lb/><hi hand= "redPen">F</hi>ebruary 16, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday </date>
               <lb/><figure>
                  <figDesc>This drawing is a man holding a bug that is standing under a tree. This
                     image is hand-drawn with some color.</figDesc>
                  <graphic
                     url="https://newtfire.org/courses/tutorials/TEI-images/mary-behrend-calendar-1909/IMG_2042.jpg"
                  />
               </figure>
               <lb/><name>Mr. Behrend</name> finds a <lb/> ??? bug! <lb/><hi rend="red">? under if
                  you have found Mary lately</hi>
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div n="3" type="calenderEntry">
            <ab>
               <lb/><hi hand= "redPen">F</hi>ebruary 17, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday <lb/><figure>
                  <figDesc>There is no image or drawing on the page just text.</figDesc>
                  <graphic
                     url="https://newtfire.org/courses/tutorials/TEI-images/mary-behrend-calendar-1909/IMG_2046.jpg"
                  />
               </figure>
               <lb/>Each Morning <hi rend="underline">very</hi> early <lb/>When all is dark &amp;
               still <lb/><unclear reason="illegible">????? ??? ??</unclear> in likely blackness
               <lb/>To work at <placeName>Hammermill</placeName>
               <lb/>I really think he's very good <lb/>to get it when it's dark <lb/>for this he <hi
                  rend="underline">says</hi> he doesn't mind<lb/>
               <unclear reason="illegible">--</unclear> can't be a <hi rend="underline">lark</hi>! <lb/>
               <hi hand= "redPen">Pour Thing! is it still dark where you arise?</hi>
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div n="4" type="calenderEntry">
            <ab>
               <lb/><hi hand= "redPen">M</hi>arch 8, 1909. <lb/>Monday <lb/><figure>
                  <figDesc>There is a big red question drawn on the page.</figDesc>
                  <graphic
                     url="https://newtfire.org/courses/tutorials/TEI-images/mary-behrend-calendar-1909/IMG_2048.jpg"
                  />
               </figure>
               <hi hand= "redPen">
                  <lb/>Perhaps this is <lb/>the day, this I <lb/>think it will or <lb/>later. Love.
                     <name>M.</name></hi>
            </ab>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
</TEI>
